Rcourse_Meta_analysis_code

HelenLiu

This script is used to perform effect size calculation,ramdom effect model of effect size, sensitivity analysis, test for publication bias and subgroup analysis

R

# Packages
if (!requireNamespace('pacman', quietly = TRUE)) {
    install.packages('pacman')
}
 
pacman::p_load(tidyverse, esc, metafor, meta)

Mean, SD

Dutke et al.(2016): The final sample comprised n=29 students in the personalized text condition and n=30 students in the standard text condition. Standard Group (mean: 87.1 sd:7.6) and (Personalized Group: mean:87 sd:7.3).

esc_mean_sd(
  grp1m = 87, grp1sd = 7.3, grp1n = 29, #Mean,SD
  grp2m = 87.1, grp2sd = 7.6, grp2n = 30, #Mean,SD
  es.type="g")#
##

t

Ginns and Fraser (2010) : The personalized group scored higher on the terminology test than the non-personalized group, t(38) = 2.98, p = 0.005, d = 0.92 [0.271.58].

esc::esc_t(
  t = 2.98, #t
  totaln = 40, #
  es.type="g") #

df <- metafor::escalc( #escalc
  measure="SMD",  
  data = effect_size,
  yi= ES, #
  vi = VI,  #variance
  slab = paste("Study ID:", id)) #label

#
df <- df[order(df$yi), ]

res <- metafor::rma(
  yi,#
  vi,#variance
  method = "REML", #method="REML" is the default
  data = df)

meta

res1 <- meta::metagen(
  TE = yi,#
  seTE = sqrt(vi), #
  data = df,
  studlab = df$id,
  fixed = FALSE,
  random = TRUE, #
  prediction = TRUE, #CI
  sm = "SMD")
res1
